class Solution {
    public int[] countBits(int n) {
        int[] ans = new int[n + 1];
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            ans[i] = ans[i & (i - 1)] + 1;
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution iterates through numbers from 1 to n, using bitwise operations to count the number of 1's in the binary representation of each number. It leverages the property that `i & (i - 1)` clears the least significant 1-bit in `i`, allowing it to compute the count in constant time per number.
